  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>Shimmering energy surrounds and protects you from &amp;Reference[fey]{fey}, &amp;Reference[undead]{undead}, and creatures originating from beyond the &amp;Reference[material]{Material} Plane. For the duration, celestials, elementals, &amp;Reference[fey]{fey}, fiends, and &amp;Reference[undead]{undead} have disadvantage on attack rolls against you.</p>\n<p>You can end the spell early by using either of the following special functions.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Break &amp;Reference[enc]{Enchantment}.</strong></em> As your action, you touch a creature you can reach that is &amp;Reference[charmed]{charmed}, &amp;Reference[frightened]{frightened}, or possessed by a &amp;Reference[celestial]{celestial}, an &amp;Reference[elemental]{elemental}, a &amp;Reference[fey]{fey}, a &amp;Reference[fiend]{fiend}, or an &amp;Reference[undead]{undead}. The creature you touch is no longer &amp;Reference[charmed]{charmed}, &amp;Reference[frightened]{frightened}, or possessed by such creatures.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Dismissal.</strong></em> As your action, make a melee spell attack against a &amp;Reference[celestial]{celestial}, an &amp;Reference[elemental]{elemental}, a &amp;Reference[fey]{fey}, a &amp;Reference[fiend]{fiend}, or an &amp;Reference[undead]{undead} you can reach. On a hit, you attempt to drive the creature back to its home plane. The creature must succeed on a &amp;Reference[cha]{Charisma} saving throw or be sent back to its home plane (if it isn't there already). If they aren't on their home plane, &amp;Reference[undead]{undead} are sent to the Shadowfell, and &amp;Reference[fey]{fey} are sent to the Feywild.</p>\n</div>",
      "chat": ""
    },
